===subject:Chapter 1 Discussion 
===from:Chris Schmidt
===date:Sun Jan 19 12:19:15 2003
===message:I disagree on the notion that both parties were unwilling to compromise and that the colonies were responsible for paying for a war debt that was fought largely at their expense. Pitt’s logic was that the American’s would supply the bulk of the manpower for the Western war effort and would not be liable for the financial costs of the war, because retaining and expanding the American colonies was in the best long-term interest of the English treasury. As was illustrated in the coming years, England’s economy was heavily dependent on trade with the American colonies. Pitt knew the worth of the colonies and England’s responsibility to defend them, but also knew that he could use Colonial bodies to fill the ranks for a much cheaper war. In repayment for their bloodshed, the colonists would be reimbursed for their war costs. 
=========yorg=========
