===subject:Reply: Tyler
===from:James Pike
===date:Tue Jan 21 19:13:41 2003
===message:I agree that both parties were at fault.  Your reasoning is well stated, as well.  I also feel that the British were just as much to blame as the American colonies were.  However, I do not feel that the French and Indian War was the Briton’s war.  I believe that as colonies of Britain, the Americans were just as much concerned with the war as Britain.  After all, the Americans could either take Britain’s side or the French’s side.  Yet, they tool the British side, showing their support and want for British rule.  This could also be due to the fact that the French may have never made an offer to the Americans.  Either way, the Americans choose to fight for the British, and doing so, the war became just as much theirs as the Britons’.  They were fighting for their freedom, and the British were fighting for their lands. 
=========yorg=========
